msDesc.head: Acts and proceedings from the canonization process of St Birgitta of Sweden

supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation 1-255 in pencil takes account of the two inserted leaves at the end of the volume.

p.note: Top of page in black ink by an 18th-century or early 19th-century hand: Kongl. Biblioteket Stockholm. Below in pencil: A. 14

Top of page in black ink: F I 4us. Middle of page in black ink by a contemporary hand: 4 folio references to mentions of Katarina in the text. Lower right corner in black ink by a contemporary hand, 4 Latin words, one above the other: prius(?), virga, dyabolus,
. Lower left corner in black ink: G.

binding.p: Medieval binding. Brown leather over wooden boards. 4 double raised binds and 2 endbands. Pinclasps with anchorplates on and pins on . , lower right corner: the National Library green book label with printed and handwritten text: Hs-Bibliotheket, Stockholm. Handskrifter. Kyrkohistoria. Sv. Medeltid. , at the top in black ink: F I; in the centre a parchment label with text in black ink, partly worn off: Attestaciones b F I. On : branded on the leather: 74; on a white label, partly torn off: A 14; at the bottom in gold: A 14
binding.condition: Leather torn and cracked along the where parts are missing, making endbands and upper bind visible. Nails near protruding through the cover. The leather on and has marks from a knife (?) and is overall worn at places leaving holes through which the wooden boards are visible. Clasps and straps lost with traces left in the anchorplates on .

origin.p:
Written by Italian scribes c. 1391 in Rome , see Collijn (1924–1924)
.

provenance.p: Belonged to the library of Vadstena monastery as attested to by the Vadstena shelfmark F I 4us on the , and by F I in ink on the and on the bottom line of the label, now almost illegible.

To the Royal Chancery in 1620 and in the 1670s to the Antiquities Archive, see Collijn (1924–1924)
. The manuscript is listed in the archive's inventories: in the inventories from 1720, 90:2, and 1722, U 90:4, as 74 (as seen on ); in U 91:2:1 as G 74 (the letter G written in the lower left corner on ); in U 91:5 as 6 (as written on ). In the last two inventories, 14 has been added to the older signum. The current signum is used for the first time in Helin's inventory U 91:2:2.

acquisition.p: From the Antiquities Archive to the Royal library in 1780.

msItem.title: Summary of the canonization process of St Birgitta of Sweden
msItem.rubric: Rubricacio seu summa tocius processus canonizacionis beate Brigide de Swecia
msItem.incipit: In nomine yhesu christi Misericordis et pii Ac eius Virginis matris et Beati Ieronimi Amen. QVia dominus noster papa et Collegium Cardinalium multis et arduis que in Romane curie alueum vndique confluunt quasi torrens
msItem.explicit: ixl dies accedentibus uero singulis infra octauas dei festi ad sepulchrum ipsum. xl. dies de iniuncta sibi penitencia misericorditer Relaxamus.

note.p: The words Rubricacio seu summa are repeated above the title on and parts of the words beate brigide de are missing due to a tear in the leaf.

supportDesc.foliation: Contemporary foliation in brown-black ink (by same scribe as some of the marginal notes?): i-xxi (). is blank without original foliation. Leaf numbering in red in the lower left corner of each verso running from a ii to b v, starts on (a i was probably in the lower corner of but is now lost). Pagination running from a 4 to a 40 in pale lead point in the middle of the lower margin visible on , on some pages barely visible. eorumdem et in
supportDesc.condition: Lower quarter of leaf missing (no loss of text) on . Horizontal tear from the outer edge one quarter down on the page, ca 8 cm in length, with partial loss of text on .

handDesc.handNote: Gothic cursive. The title on is written in a highly compressed style with elaborate final s, perhaps by a different scribe.

p.note: Top of the page in an early modern hand: Nr 6.
Top margin in black ink by an early modern hand: Acta et processus Canonizationis S. Birgittae de Suecia.
Marginal notes and manicules added on almost every page by the main hand and at least one other, contemporary or near-contemporary hand.

decoDesc.p: Main text in brown-black ink. Some underlining in red on .

decoNote.p:
In the rubric a plain initial I over 2 lines in black ink with a face in profile in the counterspace. Opening initial Q in black ink with simple leaf decoration in bows and counter space.
Plain initials, E and C, in black ink extending above the line with simple leaf decoration in bow and counter space. Initial A over 2 lines with a man's face in the counter space.

msItem.title: Acts and proceedings from the canonization process of St Birgitta of Sweden
msItem.rubric: Acta et processus habitus coram Reuerendissimis in christo patribus dominis Gradensi Corphiensi et de zangro Cardinalibus Commissariis super negocio Canonizacionis Beate Brigide de Regno Swecie
msItem.incipit: In nomine domini Amen Anno a natiuitate eiusdem Millesimo Tricentesimo Septuagesimo nono. Indiccione secunda die Iouis tercio mensis marcij ponit sanctissimi in christo patris et domini nostri domini vrbani diuina prouidencia pape sexti Anno primo. In mei notarii publici et testium infrascriptorum presencia discretus vir Nereus Nerey Cursor et magister Cursorum domini nostri pape
msItem.explicit: vt predictorum copiam dicto sindico et procuratori et quibuscumque aliis eam petentibus et habere volentibus trademur predictorum petencium sumptibus et expensis.

note.p: Below final rubric on is written: Incipiunt attestaciones testium productorum et receptorum in Roma super sancto Canonizacionis pie memorie domine Brigide de Regno Swecie. Continuando folium sequens et cetera.
: A note in the margin pointing out that three supplication letters are missing here but added at the end of the book, referring to the letters added on .

msItem.title: Attestations from individual witnesses
msItem.rubric: Incipiunt deposiciones testium productorum et receptorum in Roma Super articulis et miraculis pie memorie domine Beate Brigide de Regno Swecie ac Super negocio canonisacionis ipsius et cetera.
msItem.incipit: In christi nomine Amen sequuntur attestaciones testium productorum super vita conuersacione et miraculis recolende memorie domine Brigide
msItem.explicit: Cetera vero signa et sigilla dictis scripturis appensa et consignata dixit ipse testis illis sibi exhibitis non cognoscere.
msItem.finalRubric: Et sic sit finis huiusmodi processus et cetera. laus christo et gloria per seculorum secula Amen.

msItem.title: Supplication letters for the canonization process of St Birgitta
msItem.rubric: littere supplicatorie pro Canonizacione beate Brigide.
msItem.incipit: Hic sequuntur tres littere Supplicatorie directe domino vrbano pape vi pro Canonizacione beate Brigide de quibus fit mencio supra folio xxiijj in margine hoc est Cxiiii. Sanctissimo in christo patri ac domino domino suo Carissimo domino vrbano
msItem.explicit: sic eciam ad placandam diuine maiestatis offensam suis sanctis precibus esse dignetur patrona misericors et favorabilis advocata. Datum Orabro Strengianensis diocesis Anno ab incarnacione Millesimo CCC Septuagesimo nono xviii die mensis Ianuarii sub Sigillis nostris.

note.p: The words hoc est Cxiiii are an addition to the incipit by another hand, after which a space of ca four lines has been left blank. Below last line of the explicit the phrase hoc est die prisce virginis is added.
On processus canonizacionis beate brigide de Swecia is written in the same style as on .

supportDesc.foliation: Contemporary foliation in brown-black ink (by main scribe ?) i-clix () and clxx-ccxxix (). Clx-clxix skipped and clxx erroneously corrected to clxi (?). Numbers lxxxix-xcv () and ci-ciii () corrected. Leaf numbering in red in the lower left corner of each verso running from b vi to r xi (), often worn off, and the last one missing on account of damage to the leaf. Reuerendis patribus
supportDesc.condition: Bottom outer corners missing (no loss of text) on . Two lengthwise tears on .

handDesc.handNote: Gothic cursive. On the title processus canonizacionis beate brigide de swecia is written in the same style and by the same scribe as the title on .

p.note: Marginal notes, nota-signs and manicules passim. In the lower outer corner of most pages a contemporary or near-contemporary hand has written a c (for correxi or something similar?). Running titles and subtitles added in the top margin by a contemporary hand.
Top outer corner in black ink by two different contemporary hands: 6 chapter references (?).

msItem.title: Instruction from cardinal Lucas de Gentilibus concerning the examination of the miracles
msItem.rubric: Notabile qualiter et quomodo miracula sanctorum debeant examinari
msItem.incipit: Modus tenendus super eo quod queritur a me videtur michi quod debeat esse talis videlicet
msItem.explicit: et isti procuratores dicta miracula sic autentico modo conscripta Remittant ad dictum dominum episcopum et monasterium quolibet anno certo tempore.
